                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <head>No. 357.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Drummond</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lenox</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 7, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note dated yesterday, inclosing two printed copies of Genera! Order No.
                    253, on the subject of the revised international regulations for the prevention
                    of collisions at sea, as issued by the Navy Department.</p>
                <p>With respect to the manner in which the Treasury Department has acted in the
                    matter, according to the information with which you have been good enough to
                    furnish me, I feel sure Her Majesty’s Government will, on my bringing it to
                    their notice, be much gratified at the attention paid to their wishes, as
                    expressed to you in my note of the 24th ultimo, and the endeavors shown by the
                    Treasury Department to harmonize matters so far as they possibly can do so
                    consistently with the provisions of section 4233 of the Revised Statutes.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>VICTOR DRUMMOND.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
